holding paddock
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:an enclosure where stock are held temporarily [in preparation for drafting, shearing or similar work or where animals are held en route to a sale.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: accommodation paddock
